            <div type="edition" xml:lang="tam-Latn" rendition="class:tamil maturity:vernacular">
                
                <p>
                    <lb n="1"/>poykai A<unclear>ruḷāḷa</unclear>rai puṉaintu puttūrum Aiyyamaṟa koṇṭu Avarkku Ūrākkiṉāṉ ceyyamalarmātuyār niṉṟa malaināṭṭu vāḻ
                    <lb n="2"/>vaṇikan ĀtiIrāman keraḷan <g type="pc">.</g>
                </p>
                
            </div>
            
            <div type="apparatus"/>
                
            
            
            <div type="translation" source="bib:Hultzsch1890_01">
                
                <p>The merchant <hi rend="bold">Ādi-Rāma</hi> the <hi rend="bold">Keraḷa</hi>, who lived in <hi rend="bold">Malai-nāḍu</hi>, where the goddess with the red flower (<hi rend="italic">Lakshmī</hi>) resides, having decorated <hi rend="bold">Aruḷāḷar</hi> (<hi rend="italic">of</hi>) <hi rend="bold">Poygai</hi>, and having acquired as exclusive property (<hi rend="italic">the village of</hi>) <hi rend="bold">Puttūr</hi>, made it his (<hi rend="italic">the god's</hi>) village.</p>
                
            </div>
            
